HEADWORD: Pelicosauria
<hw>Pel`i*co*sau"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>peli`ka</grk> a wooden bowl (but taken to mean,
pelvis) + <grk>say^ros</grk> a lizard.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld>
<def>A suborder of Theromorpha, including terrestrial reptiles from the
Permian formation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

